# Project Structure Guidelines

## Main Application Structure

The project follows Next.js 15 app directory structure:

- Main entry point: [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx)
- Layout configuration: [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx)
- Global styles: [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)
- Components directory: [src/components/](mdc:src/components/)

## Static Assets Reference

The [static/](mdc:static/) directory contains reference files from the original website:

### CSS References
- [static/css/main.css](mdc:static/css/main.css) - Main stylesheet reference
- [static/css/style.css](mdc:static/css/style.css) - Additional styles reference
- [static/css/styles.css](mdc:static/css/styles.css) - Component styles reference

### JavaScript References
- [static/js/](mdc:static/js/) - Contains original JavaScript functionality
- Use as reference for implementing React/Next.js equivalents

### Media Assets
- [static/images/](mdc:static/images/) - Image assets
- [static/media/](mdc:static/media/) - Video assets
- [public/](mdc:public/) - Next.js public assets

## Component Organization

- Place reusable components in [src/components/](mdc:src/components/)
- Use TypeScript for all components (.tsx extension)
- Follow Next.js component naming conventions
- Implement proper component composition and reusability

## File Naming Conventions

- Use PascalCase for component files: `Header.tsx`, `Navigation.tsx`
- Use camelCase for utility files and hooks
- Use kebab-case for page routes (following Next.js conventions)